name may have been confused with   Haworth  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Chaworth was born about 1271, in Alfreton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas de Chaworth and joan. He married Joan in 1290. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1315, in Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"Abt 1271–1315":"umbes 1271–1315","1271–1315":"1271–1315","–1315":"–1315","1290–1347":"1290–1347","1206–1315":"1206–1315","1206":"1206","before 1315":"enne 1315","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","Abt 1271":"umbes 1271","1271":"1271","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","1290":"1290","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alfreton, Derbyshire, England":"Alfreton, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beauchief, Derbyshire, , England":"Beauchief, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1271–1315":"noin 1271–1315","1271–1315":"1271–1315","–1315":"–1315","1290–1347":"1290–1347","1206–1315":"1206–1315","1206":"1206","before 1315":"ennen vuotta 1315","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","Abt 1271":"noin 1271","1271":"1271","Abt 1290":"noin 1290","1290":"1290","Nottinghamshire, Eng